                <section id="Horizon_Plugin_concept_conbody_section_4">
            <title><ph conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/> Horizon Plugin</title>
            <p><ph conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                    /> comes with a plugin for the OpenStack Horizon dashboard. The plugin extends the main dashboard in OpenStack with a view for monitoring. This enables <ph
                    conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                    /> users to access the monitoring functions from a central Web-based graphical user interface. For details, refer to the <xref
                    format="html" href="http://docs.openstack.org/developer/horizon/" scope="external"
                            ><u><i>OpenStack Horizon documentation</i></u></xref>.</p>
            <p>Based on OpenStack Horizon, the monitoring data is visualized on a comfortable and easy-to-use dashboard which fully integrates with the following applications:<ul>
                    <li>Grafana (for metrics data). An open source application for visualizing large-scale measurement data.</li>
                    <li>Kibana (for log data). An open source analytics and visualization platform designed to work with Elasticsearch.</li>
                </ul></p>
